trailingComments.value:
* Border pattern. * * @class * @classdesc The Border pattern on a flag describes a border around each edge of the field. *
* If multiple Divisions are ever combined on a flag, the Border pattern should likely be * drawn last to provide a frame effect. * @augments Division * @namespace Division.Border

leadingComments.value:
*
     * Creates Border.
     *
     * @example
     * // Instantiates a Border
     * const border = new Border(20);
     * @param {string} color - A hex color value.
     * @param {number} borderWidth - A number representing the size of the border. This is used for coordinate drawing on a canvas for now.
     * @augments Division
     * @todo Handle border width more elegantly than taking a flat value from the caller.
